    "question": "Write a method that takes a string as an argument and groups the number of time each character appears in the string as a hash sorted by the highest number of occurrences.\n\nThe characters should be sorted alphabetically e.g:\n\n```python\nget_char_count(\"cba\") == {1: [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"]}\n```\n\nYou should ignore spaces, special characters and count uppercase letters as lowercase ones.\n\nFor example: \n```python\nget_char_count(\"Mississippi\")           ==  {4: [\"i\", \"s\"], 2: [\"p\"], 1: [\"m\"]}\nget_char_count(\"Hello. Hello? HELLO!\")  ==  {6: [\"l\"], 3: [\"e\", \"h\", \"o\"]}\nget_char_count(\"aaa...bb...c!\")         ==  {3: [\"a\"], 2: [\"b\"], 1: [\"c\"]}\nget_char_count(\"abc123\")                ==  {1: [\"1\", \"2\", \"3\", \"a\", \"b\", \"c\"]}\nget_char_count(\"aaabbbccc\")             ==  {3: [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"]}\n```",
